Loomer shared screenshots of caps with '8647' on Amazon, tagging Jeff Bezos. Comey's post, interpreted by some as a threat to Trump, sparked outrage. Elon Musk also criticized Comey's post, calling it a serious crime.
title: Trump ally slams Jeff Bezos for 'assassination gear on Amazon'; says: Wow ...

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: The US Senate has moved forward with the Genius Act, a bill designed to regulate stablecoins. Despite Democratic concerns about President Trump's potential conflicts of interest due to his cryptocurrency ventures, the bill passed a key procedural vote. It introduces comprehensive regulations for stablecoins, including reserve requirements and consumer protections.
title: What is Stablecoin Regulation Bill? US Senate advances cryptocurrency legislation

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Following discussions between parliamentary affairs minister Kiren Rijiju and TMC chief Mamata Banerjee, the Trinamool Congress has nominated Abhishek Banerjee to represent the party in parliamentary delegations related to Operation Sindoor. This decision follows Banerjee's emphasis on the need for inclusive consultations in selecting delegation members. He also suggested including family members of martyrs and officers involved in Operation Sindoor.
title: Abhishek Banerjee to represent TMC in all-party delegation on Operation Sindoor

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: The Indian Army's Chinar Corps executed Operation Sindoor, decimating military infrastructure in Pakistan-Occupied Kashmir's Leepa Valley, including posts, ammunition depots, and fuel storage. Officials estimate it will take Pakistan 8-12 months to rebuild, following retaliation for ceasefire violations. India also destroyed nine terror camps in Pakistan and PoK in response to the Pahalgam terror attack.
title: 'Army 'fully destroyed' military infra in PoK's Leepa Valley during Op Sindoor'

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: An IPL 2025 match between Sunrisers Hyderabad and Lucknow Super Giants saw a fiery confrontation between Abhishek Sharma and Digvesh Rathi, sparked by Rathi's aggressive celebrations. Both players faced penalties, with Rathi receiving a heavier fine and suspension.
title: IPL on-field spat: Before Rathi-Abhishek was Kieron Pollard-Mitchell Starc

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Abhishek Sharma's explosive half-century and Heinrich Klaasen's composed innings propelled Sunrisers Hyderabad to a six-wicket victory over Lucknow Super Giants, eliminating LSG from playoff contention. Despite Mitchell Marsh and Aiden Markram's fifties setting a strong foundation, Lucknow's late-over collapse proved costly. SRH successfully chased down the target, marking their first 200-plus chase at the Ekana Stadium.
title: 'It's been challenging': Sanjiv Goenka on LSG's elimination

author: IP SINGH
description: In Punjab's Jalandhar, a woman, along with the village sarpanch and a panchayat member, has been booked for allegedly attempting to obtain a false death certificate for her husband. Kuldeep Singh, who emigrated to the US via the 'dunki route' in 1998, never returned to India due to residency issues.
title: Punjab woman declares husband in US ‘dead’ for property

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Ali Khan Mahmudabad, an Ashoka University professor, was arrested by Haryana Police following a social media post about Operation Sindoor, which was perceived as critical of the military. The arrest, based on a complaint from a BJP Yuva Morcha leader, has ignited controversy and sparked widespread support for Mahmudabad from students and colleagues.
title: Who is Ali Khan Mahmudabad? Ashoka Univ prof arrested over 'Op Sindoor' remark

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Indian authorities have arrested at least 12 individuals across Punjab, Haryana, and Uttar Pradesh for alleged espionage linked to Pakistan. The suspects, including a YouTuber, are accused of sharing sensitive information with Pakistani Intelligence Operatives. Investigations revealed contact with a Pakistani official at the Pakistan High Commission in Delhi, who has since been expelled.
title: YouTuber, trader, student, security guard: 12 'spies' come from all walks of life

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: India's first bullet train project, connecting Mumbai and Ahmedabad, has achieved a significant milestone with 300 km of viaduct work completed, announced Railway Minister Ashwini Vaishnaw. The project, executed by NHSRCL, also includes the completion of a 350-meter mountain tunnel and the installation of India's first reinforced concrete track bed using Japanese Shinkansen technology.
title: 300km viaduct completed: Sneak peek into India’s first bullet train project - Watch

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Citing an unnamed source familiar with the talks, the Washington Post said that US officials have told Israel it could lose American backing if the conflict does not stop. "Trump's people are letting Israel know, 'We will abandon you if you do not end this war,'" the source was quoted as saying by the Washington Post.
title: Did US threaten to 'abandon' Israel if it continues war in Gaza?

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Gold rate today: Gold futures on MCX opened lower, while silver also saw a decline. Prices have fluctuated, influenced by Moody's US credit rating downgrade and Russia-Ukraine peace talk hopes.
title: Gold rates plunged over Rs 6,500 from all time high; where is it headed?

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: The Indian Army's bomb disposal squad safely detonated a live shell fired from Pakistan near a village in Jammu and Kashmir's Poonch district, averting a potential disaster. Residents expressed relief and gratitude, highlighting the army's crucial role in safeguarding the community.
title: 'It was a huge threat': Army destroys live Pakistani shell in J&K's Poonch

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Rajasthan Royals' Jofra Archer delighted fans by mimicking Ravindra Jadeja's bowling action during a practice session, showcasing his playful side. The amusing video, shared by Rajasthan Royals, quickly went viral. In IPL 2025, Chennai Super Kings and Rajasthan Royals are set to clash at the Arun Jaitley Stadium. For CSK, the 2025 season has been largely disappointing, with all departments faltering.
title: Jofra Archer mimics Ravindra Jadeja's bowling and nails it perfectly

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Microsoft's Build 2025 event faced disruption as an employee, Joe Lopez, protested against the company's contracts with the Israeli government, shouting slogans like 'Free Palestine'. This follows similar protests at Microsoft's 50th-anniversary celebrations. Lopez, a Microsoft Azure veteran, claims the company's technology aids in harming Palestinian civilians, a claim Microsoft denies.
title: Microsoft CEO Satya Nadella’s Build 2025 speech disrupted by 'free Palestine' protest

author: LAKSHIMA SAREEN
description: Despite progress in university enrollment, a UNESCO report highlights a persistent gender gap in STEM fields globally. Women are underrepresented in engineering, technical training, and digital skills, particularly in low-income countries. Even with STEM education, they face barriers to leadership roles. Systemic changes, including mentorship and flexible policies, are crucial to ensure women can fully contribute to innovation and progress.
title: STEMming the Tide: Why women are still missing from labs and leadership

author: TRISHA TEWARI
description: The UPSC has declared the final results of the Indian Forest Service Examination 2024, recommending 143 candidates for appointment across various categories. The top rank was secured by Kanika Anabh. The result follows a rigorous selection process, including written exams and interviews. Two PwBD vacancies remain unfilled and will carry over to the next recruitment cycle.
title: UPSC Indian forest service exam 2024 result: Toppers and other details

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: H-1B visa applications for FY26 have significantly decreased, influenced by stricter regulations under Donald Trump's policies and increased application costs. Heightened scrutiny, including social media verification and rigorous documentation, contributes to the decline, alongside economic factors like tech industry layoffs.
title: Why have H-1B visa applications plunged? Blame it on Trump!

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Lucknow Super Giants bowler Digvesh Rathi has been penalised for violating the IPL Code of Conduct during a match against Sunrisers Hyderabad. He was fined 50% of his match fees and suspended for one game due to accumulating five demerit points this season.
title: Digvesh Rathi suspended for one match after spat with Abhishek Sharma

author: TNN
description: Jayant Narlikar, the esteemed astrophysicist and founder of IUCAA, died in Pune on Tuesday. Born in 1938, he studied at Cambridge and later contributed significantly to cosmology, advocating alternative models to the Big Bang theory. Narlikar was also a celebrated science communicator and author, survived by his three daughters, all scientists, following the passing of his wife in 2023.
title: Noted astrophysicist Jayant Narlikar passes away at 87 in Pune

author: YUDHVIR RANA
description: Punjab Police busted a Babbar Khalsa International (BKI) terror module in Batala, arresting six members after a shootout. The module, backed by Pakistan's ISI, operated under foreign-based handlers Maninder Billa and Mannu Agwan, directed by Harwinder Singh Rinda. The arrested individuals were involved in grenade attacks, logistics, and financing.
title: 'Operated by foreign-based handlers': Pak-backed terror module busted in Punjab

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Protean eGov Technologies' shares have plummeted over 30% in two days after the Income Tax Department rejected their bid for the PAN 2.0 systems upgrade project. This decline erases the stock's gains from the past year.
title: Protean eGov shares plummet 30% after not being selected for PAN 2.0 project

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Shreyas Iyer has achieved a unique milestone by leading Punjab Kings to the IPL 2025 playoffs, marking his third franchise to reach this stage. Sunil Gavaskar highlighted Iyer's underappreciated role in KKR's previous title win, emphasizing his on-field leadership. Iyer praised his team's unity and support after their victory over Rajasthan Royals, urging them to maintain momentum.
title: Sunil Gavaskar fires shots at KKR over Shreyas Iyer snub

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: The Indian Air Force (IAF) released a video showcasing Operation Sindoor, its response to a Pakistan-backed terror attack in Pahalgam that killed 26. The IAF conducted precision strikes on terror-linked sites in Pakistan and Pakistan-Occupied Kashmir, including Jaish-e-Mohammed and Lashkar-e-Taiba locations. Pakistan retaliated, leading to further IAF strikes on radar installations and airbases.
title: 'Unseen, unstoppable': IAF showcases combat prowess, precision strikes in new video

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: 'War 2’ Teaser:  Hrithik Roshan and Jr NTR are set to ignite screens in 'War 2', the sixth installment of the YRF Spy Universe, directed by Ayan Mukerji. Jr NTR's Bollywood debut as the antagonist promises a clash of titans. The film boasts globe-trotting espionage, high-octane action sequences, and a musical face-off composed by Pritam.
title: 'War 2’ Teaser: Hrithik, Jr NTR & Kiara's power-packed first glimpse is out

author: RAJ SHEKHAR JHA
description: The arrest of YouTuber Jyoti Malhotra for allegedly sharing military secrets with Pakistan has echoes of the Madhuri Gupta case. Gupta, an Indian diplomat in Islamabad, was arrested in 2010 for espionage. She was honey-trapped by Pakistani intelligence, passing sensitive information after being manipulated by promises of love.
title: Long before Jyoti, Pak had honey-trapped Madhuri: Held in 2010, found guilty in 2018

author: NITHYA MANDYAM
description: Bengaluru is reeling from torrential rainfall, resulting in three fatalities, widespread flooding affecting 500 homes, and significant infrastructure disruptions. The intense downpour, exceeding stormwater drain capacity, submerged streets, uprooted trees, and halted public transport. With more rain forecast, the city grapples with outdated drainage systems struggling to manage the impact of rapid urbanization and climate change.
title: 3 dead, 500 homes flooded: Bengaluru braces for 5 more days of heavy rain

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Rishabh Pant's struggles continued as Lucknow Super Giants were eliminated from IPL 2025 playoff contention after a loss to Sunrisers Hyderabad. Pant's poor form with the bat added to LSG's woes, with his low score contributing to his disappointing season. Injuries to key bowlers further hampered LSG's chances, impacting their overall performance despite a strong batting lineup.
title: Rishabh Pant's worst IPL season: How much is he costing per run scored?

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Stock market today: Nifty50 and BSE Sensex, the Indian equity benchmark indices, opened in green on Tuesday. While Nifty50 went above 25,000, BSE Sensex was above 82,000.
title: Stock market today: Nifty50 opens in green; BSE Sensex above 82,000

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Averted disaster struck in Uttar Pradesh's Hardoi district as vigilant loco pilots foiled attempts to derail two passenger trains, including the Rajdhani Express. Wooden blocks tied to the tracks with earthing wires were spotted by the Rajdhani Express pilot, who applied emergency brakes. A similar attempt targeting the Kathgodam Express was also thwarted.
title: Wooden blocks on tracks: Plot to derail 2 trains foiled in UP

author: ANJALI SINGH
description: Ali Khan Mahmudabad, a professor at Ashoka University, was arrested following a complaint. The complaint was filed by Haryana State Women's Commission chairperson Renu Bhatia. It alleges his comments on Operation Sindoor endangered India's sovereignty. Colleagues are providing support to Mahmudabad. They are ensuring his well-being while he is in custody. The faculty association has condemned the arrest.
title: Ashoka University professor in lockup, colleagues keep vigil at police station in shifts

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: In today's fast-paced world, forest bathing, or Shinrin-yoku, offers a powerful antidote to urban pollution and sedentary lifestyles. This Japanese practice involves mindful immersion in nature, promoting physical and psychological well-being. Scientific studies reveal that forest environments enhance immune function and improve respiratory health, making it a valuable preventive medicine.
title: Breathe, walk, heal: Forest bathing, Japan’s lush prescription for modern-day burnout

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Stock market recommendations: Mirae Asset Sharekhan suggests buying Dabur and Gail. Dabur, trading between Rs 480-488, is expected to resume its uptrend after breaking a downward trendline, targeting Rs 519. Similarly, Gail, recommended in the Rs 188-191 range, anticipates an upward movement to Rs 213 following a bullish flag pattern breakout, supported by positive momentum indicators.
title: Buy or sell: Stock market recommendations for today

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: India and the US are engaged in trade deal negotiations, aiming to finalize an initial agreement before July, when US tariffs take effect. The proposed deal is structured in three phases, addressing industrial goods, agricultural products, and non-tariff barriers. Discussions are ongoing, with hopes for a broader agreement by autumn, potentially coinciding with a Quad summit visit.
title: India eyes three-phase trade deal with US as Trump’s reciprocal tariffs loom

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: India's ambassador to Israel, JP Singh, asserted that Operation Sindoor, initiated in response to Pakistan's cross-border terrorism, remains paused, not concluded. He urged a global coalition against terrorism, demanding Pakistan hand over key figures like Hafiz Saeed. Singh highlighted India's firm stance against terrorism, emphasizing that treaties require an end to Pakistan's support for terrorist activities.
title: Indian envoy demands Hafiz Saeed's extradition, asks if US did it, why can't Pakistan?

author: DISHANK PUROHIT
description: Rajasthan Police have arrested a 23-year-old woman, Anuradha Paswan, in Bhopal for allegedly defrauding 25 men across multiple states within seven months. Dubbed the "loot-and-scoot bride," she targeted desperate grooms, marrying them and fleeing with valuables shortly after the wedding.
title: Married 25 men in 7 months: 'Loot and scoot' bride arrested in Rajasthan

author: AMIT ANAND CHOUDHARY
description: The Supreme Court clarified on Monday that there's no mandatory one-year jail term before bail in money laundering cases, granting relief to an accused in the Chhattisgarh liquor scam. Justices Oka and Bhuyan emphasized that a year-long custody isn't a prerequisite for bail.
title: '1-year jail not a prerequisite for bail to accused in laundering case': SC to ED

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: In an IPL 2025 match where SRH defeated LSG, eliminating them from playoff contention, a heated moment occurred. Young cricketers Abhishek Sharma and Digvesh Rathi engaged in a confrontation after Rathi dismissed Sharma. BCCI Vice-President Rajeev Shukla intervened, mediating a reconciliation between the two players. Abhishek, despite not reaching his peak performance in IPL 2025, has maintained better batting statistics compared to his SRH teammates. He aims to finish strong in the team's final two matches of the season.
title: Ceasefire! BCCI VP steps in to end Abhishek–Digvesh Rathi fight

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Lt Gen Sumer Ivan D'Cunha asserted India's capability to strike any target within Pakistan, emphasizing the nation's preparedness to respond across the entire depth of Pakistani territory if needed. Operation Sindoor showcased India's use of locally developed technology, including long-range drones and guided munitions, to strike key Pakistani airbases.
title: 'From Rawalpindi to Khyber Pakhtunkhwa, India can strike anywhere in Pak'

description: Lucknow Super Giants' defeat has intensified the IPL 2025 playoff race, eliminating them from contention. Gujarat Titans, Royal Challengers Bengaluru, and Punjab Kings have already qualified, leaving one spot open. Mumbai Indians and Delhi Capitals are now in a fierce battle, with their head-to-head match on May 21st crucial for determining who advances to the playoffs.

description: Asked about reports that China may have provided satellite and air defence support to Pakistan during the conflict, the official said that since tensions started to increase between India and Pakistan, China followed an "objective and just position, urged the two countries to exercise calm and restraint, and avoid escalation".
title: India, Pakistan both key neighbours, will help keep peace: China

author: VISHWA MOHAN
description: Days after calling the 1960 treaty a "historic mistake", Union agriculture minister Shivraj Singh Chouhan on Monday met farmers organisations and explained to them how the then PM Jawaharlal Nehru signed the treaty despite opposition from experts. He said that Nehru not only agreed to give water to Pakistan at the cost of India but also gave Rs 83 crore to the neighbouring country, whose value now amounts to Rs 5,500 crore.

description: Former teammate Joginder Sharma suggests MS Dhoni should consider retirement after Chennai Super Kings' disappointing IPL season, where they failed to reach the playoffs. Dhoni's future has been questioned, especially with his altered batting position and coach's concerns about his endurance. Joginder, who bowled the iconic final over under Dhoni’s captaincy in the 2007 T20 World Cup final, feels the veteran wicketkeeper-batter should call time on his illustrious 18-year IPL career.

author: TIMESOFINDIA.COM
description: While upholding the trial court's survey order, Justice Rohit Ranjan Agarwal vacated the interim stay on the Hindu plaintiffs' suit. The mosque committee had asked for the suit to be dismissed on the ground that the Hindu side's claim to the site was prima facie barred under the Places of Worship Act, 1991. The legislation prohibits conversion of any place of worship and mandates maintaining the religious character of any such site that existed on Aug 15, 1947.
title: Plaintiffs only seeking right to access to Sambhal site: HC upholds trial court order

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: During the IPL 2025 match between LSG and SRH, a heated exchange erupted between Digvesh Rathi and Abhishek Sharma after Rathi dismissed Sharma. Sharma, visibly upset by Rathi's celebration, was caught on camera uttering threats. This incident overshadowed impressive performances from Mitchell Marsh, Aiden Markram, and Nicholas Pooran for LSG, as well as Sharma's explosive innings for SRH.
